article.headline: UC Irvine 68, UC Davis 61
article.story: IRVINE, Calif. -- Chris McNealy scored 13 of his 16 points in the second half and UC Irvine came up with a 20-9 run to finish the game for a 68-61 victory over UC Davis on Thursday night. UC Davis (1-20, 0-9 Big West) had a four-point lead with about six minutes to play before UC Irvine made its charge. UC Irvine (9-13, 5-4) got 13 points from Daman Starring, 12 points from Michael Wilder and 11 points from Adam Folker, who also had eight rebounds. Josh Ritchart had four 3-pointers for UC Davis, three in the second half. He led his team with 14 points. Harrison DuPont and Eddie Miller each scored 11.
